==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greenfinch
<hw>Green"finch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A European finch (<spn>Ligurinus chloris</spn>); --
called also <altname>green bird</altname>, <altname>green
linnet</altname>, <altname>green grosbeak</altname>, <altname>green
olf</altname>, <altname>greeny</altname>, and
<altname>peasweep</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The Texas sparrow (<spn>Embernagra
rufivirgata</spn>), in which the general color is olive green, with four
rufous stripes on the head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greenfish</ent>⟦br⟧
